.TH "NAVIGATIONTRANSITION" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationTransition \- NavigationTransition
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]NavigationTransition\f[B]\f[R] interface of the
Navigation API represents an ongoing navigation, that is, a navigation
that hasn\(cqt yet reached the \f[CR]navigatesuccess\f[R] or
\f[CR]navigateerror\f[R] stage.
.PP
It is accessed via the \f[CR]Navigation.transition\f[R] property.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]finished\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns a \f[CR]Promise\f[R] that fulfills at the same time the
\f[CR]navigatesuccess\f[R] event fires, or rejects at the same time the
\f[CR]navigateerror\f[R] event fires.
.TP
\f[B]from\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the \f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] that the transition is
coming from.
.TP
\f[B]navigationType\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the type of the ongoing navigation.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]async\f[R] \f[B]function\f[R] cleanupNavigation() {
  \f[B]await\f[R] navigation.transition.finished;
  \f[I]// Navigation has completed successfully\f[R]
  \f[I]// Cleanup any ongoing monitoring\f[R]
}
.EE
